===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
Two theories:
*{{liushu|p|nocap=1}} of an acorn. Compare {{zh-l|櫟}}.
*A human head. Compare {{zh-l|皃}} ({{zh-l|貌}}) and {{zh-l|黑}}.

Possibly part of a phonetic family contrasting stop initials (P/B) for exposure/brightness against nasal initials (M) for concealment/darkness; compare {{och-l|黑|tr=*m̥ˤək}} and {{och-l|白|tr=*bˤrak}}.

===Etymology===
STEDT derives it from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*bawk||white}}, whence also {{cog|tbq-bdg-pro|*bok||white}}, {{cog|lif|ᤑ||tr=phô|white}}; also compare {{cog|mkh-pro|*kɓɔɔk||white, grey}}.

However, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} finds it difficult to reconcile these forms with {{cog|ltc|-}} due to the lack of medial ''r''. Instead, he proposes a derivation from {{der|zh|sit-pro|*(p/b/h)(w/j)a(ː)(r/l/n/t)|*bar|white}} with ''-k'' extension, thus cognate with {{och-l|皤|gloss=white|id=2}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}), {{cog|lus|vâr||(to be) white}}, {{cog|kar-pro|*ʔ(b)wa||white}}.

